MEDTRUST PROJECT FULL REPORT
Date: March 14, 2026
Repository: https://github.com/VaibhavN17/medTrust.git
Branch: main

======================================================================
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
======================================================================
MedTrust is a full-stack donation transparency platform focused on
medical fundraising. It enables patients to create campaigns, NGOs/admins
to verify and moderate those campaigns, and donors to contribute through
Razorpay with visibility into expenses and updates.

The project currently includes:
- A Node.js + Express + MySQL backend API
- A Next.js frontend web application (App Router)
- Dockerized deployment for frontend, backend, and MySQL
- Role-based workflows for patient, donor, ngo, and admin
- Donation flow with signature verification and receipts

Operational status at report time:
- Backend container running and healthy on port 5000
- Frontend container running on port 3000
- MySQL container healthy, exposed on host port 3307

======================================================================
2. PROJECT OBJECTIVES AND BUSINESS VALUE
======================================================================
Primary objective:
- Build trust in medical crowdfunding through verification and spend
  transparency.

Key value propositions:
- Verified campaigns before fundraising activation
- Every donation mapped to a campaign and payment status
- Expense receipts and update timelines visible to donors/public
- Fraud-flag mechanism and admin oversight controls

======================================================================
3. TECHNICAL STACK
======================================================================
Frontend:
- Next.js 14 (React 18, TypeScript)
- Tailwind CSS
- Zustand for client auth state
- Axios for API communication
- Razorpay checkout integration

Backend:
- Node.js + Express
- MySQL 8 (mysql2)
- JWT-based authentication
- express-validator for request validation
- multer / multer-s3 for file uploads
- Nodemailer for email notifications
- Razorpay SDK for payment order and verification

Infrastructure and operations:
- Docker + Docker Compose
- MySQL container with schema bootstrap from schema.sql
- Separate frontend and backend Docker images

