Donation and payment:
- Donation order creation
- Razorpay signature verification
- Captured-payment persistence
- Donor donation history
- Public campaign donor list
- Minimum donation support: Rs 1

Transparency and governance:
- Expense record and receipt uploads
- Fraud flagging and status management
- Admin statistics and moderation screens

Email notifications:
- Welcome, campaign status, donation receipt workflows

======================================================================
7. API SURFACE SUMMARY
======================================================================
Measured route definitions in backend router: 28

Domain groupings:
- Auth
  /auth/register, /auth/login, /auth/me, /auth/profile, /auth/password

- Campaigns
  /campaigns, /campaigns/mine, /campaigns/:id,
  /campaigns/:campaign_id/documents,
  /campaigns/:campaign_id/updates

- Donations
  /donations/order, /donations/verify, /donations/mine,
  /campaigns/:campaign_id/donations

- Expenses
  /campaigns/:campaign_id/expenses (GET/POST)

- NGO
  /ngo/pending, /ngo/verify/:id, /ngo/reject/:id, /ngo/flag/:campaign_id

- Admin
  /admin/stats, /admin/users, /admin/users/:id/toggle,
  /admin/campaigns, /admin/fraud-flags, /admin/fraud-flags/:id

======================================================================
8. DATABASE DESIGN SUMMARY
======================================================================
Measured tables in schema.sql: 10

Core entities:
- users
- ngo_profiles
- campaigns
- documents
- donations
- expenses
- campaign_updates
- ngo_verifications
- fraud_flags
- notifications

Key design notes:
- Role model supports patient/donor/ngo/admin
- FK constraints enforce referential integrity
- Donation table records payment IDs and verification signature
- Campaign table tracks verification status and raised amount
- Full-text index supports campaign search in key text fields

